title: Grateful Dead Live at Felt Forum, Madison Square Garden on 1971-12-05
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Beat It On Down The Line, Big Boss Man, Brown Eyed Women, Muddy Water, Jack Straw, Mr. Charlie, Tennessee Jed, El Paso, Deal, Playin' In The Band, Next Time You See Me, Comes A Time, Casey Jones, One More Saturday Night

Set 2

Truckin', Ramble On Rose, It Hurts Me Too, Sugaree, Sugar Magnolia, Dark Star Jam-> Me & My Uncle-> Dark Star Jam-> Sitting On Top Of The World, Me And Bobby McGee, Big Railroad Blues, Mexicali Blues, You Win Again, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: Johnny B. Goode

FM broadcast WNEW-New York - Other artist(s): NRPS

reviews.review_text: Thank you Thank you Mr. Charlie for yet another much needed upgrade of one of the all-time classic shows!
sittin on top of the world check it out. im not aware of a better one
Another Solid Show Highlights:  Washed My Hands In Muddy Water, One More Saturday Night
Best Version This is the definitive version of this show...thanks, as always Charlie Miller.

12/5/71 Felt Forum This is classic 71'/72' Dead.I can't believe someone downplayed this show with 3 stars.Why bother reviewing the show or even listening for that matter? 7 gold stars to make up for the shortsightedness of previous reviewers.

ubiquitous Excellent version of a classic show. This was one of the most ubiquitous tapes of the 70s, pretty much every New York head had this. For a lot of us these early readings of songs like Jack Straw, Sugaree and Tennessee Jed were just as definitive as the official versions, and Comes a Time is still THE version for me. Definitely a band in transition, Keith Godchaux was just coming into his own and of course they hit another peak altogether in 1972, but this gets 5 stars for its historical importance.
